### ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
### Local Testing for CatalogService (Products)
### Requires VS Code "REST Client" or BAS built-in HTTP client
### ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

@server = http://localhost:4004
# 'alice' is a default mock user provided by the CAP framework for local testing
@auth = Basic alice:

### 1. Get all Products (Should return empty array initially)
GET {{server}}/odata/v4/catalog/Products
Authorization: {{auth}}

### 2. Create a new Product
# @name createProduct
POST {{server}}/odata/v4/catalog/Products
Authorization: {{auth}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "The Hitchhiker's Guide to the Galaxy",
  "description": "A comedic science fiction franchise created by Douglas Adams.",
  "price": 42.00,
  "stock": 100
}

### 3. Read the newly created Product
# Grabs the ID automatically from the previous POST request
@productId = {{createProduct.response.body.ID}}

GET {{server}}/odata/v4/catalog/Products({{productId}})
Authorization: {{auth}}

### 4. Update the Product's stock (e.g., someone bought a copy)
PATCH {{server}}/odata/v4/catalog/Products({{productId}})
Authorization: {{auth}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "stock": 99
}

### 5. Delete the Product
DELETE {{server}}/odata/v4/catalog/Products({{productId}})
Authorization: {{auth}}

### ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
### 6. Test Unauthorized Access (Should return 401 Unauthorized)
### ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
GET {{server}}/odata/v4/catalog/Products